         <sourceDesc>
            <msDesc xml:id="ms">
               <msIdentifier>
                  <repository ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0447EMIP">Rendel B. Alldredge Psalter</repository>
                  <collection>EMIP</collection>
                  <idno facs="EMIP/Codices/3244/" n="155" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/api/iiif/EMIP03244/manifest">Rendel B. Alldredge Psalter</idno>
               </msIdentifier>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="3r" to="138r" facs="003">Fols 3r–138r</locus><title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2701Dawit">Psalter</title>
                    <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                    <note>Fragment of a Psalter, though there is not actually any evidence that this Psalter ever had more than the first three works shown here</note>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1"><locus from="3r" to="114v" facs="003">Fols 3r–114v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</title>
                      <note>The psalms begin with the traditional heading, but with the addition of <foreign xml:lang="gez">አርአያ</foreign></note>
                      <note><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual</span></ref> from the common new system</note>
                      <note><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps151"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps151</span></ref> contains all four of the plusses that make up the long edition</note>
                    </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2"><locus from="115r" to="129r" facs="115">Fols 115r–129r</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1828Mahale">Book of Odes</title>
                      <note>The fourth biblical canticle <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2257salota#Hannah"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2257salota#Hannah</span></ref> is <q>“[Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel,] Prophetess.”</q></note>
                    </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3"><locus from="129v" to="138r" facs="130">Fols 129v–138r</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2362Songof">Song of Songs</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <note>Common Edition</note>
                </msItem>
              </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           
                        </support>
                        <extent>
                           <measure unit="leaf">141</measure>
                           <dimensions type="outer" unit="mm">
                              <height/>
                              <width/>
                              <depth/>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                       <layout columns="1" writtenLines="15 16"/>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word for God is not rubricated in the first three works</desc>
                  <desc>Nowhere is there use of columetric layout of rubricated text</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#139r" facs="139">Fol. 139r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> with two guardian angels</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#140r" facs="140">Fol. 140r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> with two guardian angels, by another artist</desc></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                      <locus target="#1v" facs="002">Fol. 1v</locus>
                      <desc>illegible text, written in pencil</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                      <locus target="#2v" facs="003">Fol. 2v</locus>
                      <desc>The front foreguard sheet (two folios) appears to be taken from another, much older book.
                      On every page there are faint remains of the text which was originally on the sheet.
                      The text on 2v seems clear enough to suggest a hand of the 16th century</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>There are marginal notations from the strophe counting system, with the number 10 appearing at regular intervals</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                      <locus target="#61r" facs="061">Fol. 61r</locus>
                      <desc>The midpoint of the Psalms is marked with a small ornamental cross in the margin</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                      <desc><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</ref> end with an added poem, <q>“the Psalms of David are like a garden.”</q>
                      with incipit <foreign xml:lang="gez">
                      ዛቲ፡ መዝሙረ፡ ዳዊት፡ ትመስል፡ ገነተ።
                      ወታስተጋብእ፡ ኵሎ፡ ጽጌያተ።
                      ወመልዕ፡ ፍሬያተ፡ ወታመጽእ፡ በረከተ።
                      ወትሰድድ፡ አጋንንተ፡ ወታቀርብ፡ መላዕክተ።
                      </foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                      <locus target="#138r" facs="138">Fol. 138r</locus>
                      <desc type="ScribalNoteCommencing">
                        at the conclusion of the <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2362Songof">Song of Songs</title>, there is a scribal notation of the timeframe of copying the book:
                        <q>This Psalter was started on Thursday, the 17th of Näḥase, and was completed on the 2nd of Pagwamen</q>
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                      <locus target="#141r" facs="141">Fol. 141r</locus>
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">Note of secondary ownership: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀሺ፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡</foreign></desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
                </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
